You might see some C++ programs that run without the standard namespace library. The using namespace std line can be omitted and replaced with the std keyword, 
followed by the :: operator 
for string (and cout) objects:

Example

  #include <iostream>#include <string>// using namespace 
  std; - Remove this lineint main() { 
  std::string greeting = "Hello";  std::cout 
  << greeting;  return 0;}
Try it Yourself »

